cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely sub-category as the paper addresses the problem of object localisation in images and videos. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel framework based on Bayesian joint topic modelling. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with learning from weakly labelled data and exploiting unlabelled data for learning. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible sub-category as the paper experiments on the YouTube-Object videos dataset. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possible sub-category as the paper discusses the exploitation of various types of prior knowledge for Bayesian domain adaptation and transfer learning.
